      "author_association": "MEMBER",
      "body": "Not public yet mostly because some of the public PRs decoupled from the all-in-one branch have led to additional improvements and bug fixes throughout the sources. Which has been great for the software as a whole but they have been time consuming. Additionally, I'm not satisfied with the high false-positive rate of the filters (our wallet produces 8k scripts from the beginning), which was one of the motivations behind #27469 and want to do more before sharing it.\r\n\r\nEssentially, I’m preferring this incremental approach as it sums value to the release cycle, and lets me solidify the bases of the work while incorporate new improvements that arise during the review process.\r\nIt might not be that “visible” but, if you check all the linked PRs, it has been quite fruitful so far.\r\n\r\nPromise to ping here once the long branch is available.",
